    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I get that, socioeconomic factors are definitely huge. But for the sake of the literature review, I need to be able to cite the actual statistical trends that show up in the datasets. Even if they're driven by poverty, there are clearly specific groups that appear more frequently in crime statistics in these urban studies. Can you outline which groups are typically identified in those correlations so I can look up the specific papers?",
